===Etymology===
A learned 17th-century coinage, {{prefix|mono|theism|lang=en}}, from ({{m|grc|μονός||one}}) and ({{m|grc|θεός||god, [[deity]]}} + {{m|grc|-ισμός}}) The term parallels the earlier [[polytheism]], [[atheism]] (the simplex [[theism]] being slightly later).
The earliest known use is by Henry More, ca. 1660, in explicit juxtaposition with both ''atheism'' and ''polytheism''.

